	"note": "Real source of SecUSo Privacy Friendly Pedometer, pinned at tag v3.1.0 (not the newer v3.1.2 -- the v3.1.0..v3.1.1 diff touches our subgraph's actual files, in a small real changeset that's used as edit 01; v3.1.1..v3.1.2 is a locale-only commit). Not the whole app (60 source files spanning charts/fragments/tutorial/backup-api) -- an acyclic real SUBGRAPH covering the distinctive behaviors this app was picked for: the foreground step-detection Service (health), the step SENSOR listener, AlarmManager-scheduled receivers, legacy SQLite persistence, and a home-screen widget. Same technique as sora-editor-lib: pin real leaf files, author minimal scaffolding only where the real files reference UI classes outside the subgraph (MainActivity/TrainingActivity/SplashActivity are stand-in Activities here -- the real files only ever construct Intent/PendingIntent targeting them, never call into their bodies; adapters.TrainingOverviewAdapter is a stand-in for a single constant field, avoiding a RecyclerView adapter + 3 icon-heavy card layouts that Training.java doesn't otherwise need). Excludes :backup-api (same rationale as the 2048/notes/etc entries) and androidx.work/MPAndroidChart/multidex (unused by this subgraph). Needs androidx.appcompat + androidx.legacy.legacy-support-v4 (WakefulBroadcastReceiver) + com.google.android.material on the compile classpath. Only mdpi icons vendored. attrs.xml does not exist yet at v3.1.0 (edit 01 creates it).",
